text: West Kalimantan () is a province of Indonesia. It is one of five Indonesian provinces in Kalimantan, the Indonesian part of the island of Borneo. Its capital city is Pontianak. The province has an area of with a recorded 2010 census population of 4,395,983. The latest official population estimate (as of January 2014) is 4,546,439. == References == == Other websites == * Go West Kalimantan * Kalimantan as a Tourism Destination Category:Provinces of Indonesia Category:Kalimantan
